Today, I worked on a complete data cleaning and machine learning workflow using a real-world dataset.

I started by cleaning the dataset:

* Renamed and standardized column names
* Handled missing values using methods like dropping and median filling
* Removed unnecessary or irrelevant columns
* Converted data types (e.g., date formatting)
* Checked for duplicates and inconsistencies
* Encoded categorical variables into numerical format
* Ensured the dataset was fully clean with no null values remaining

After preprocessing, I moved to model building:

* Split the data into training and testing sets
* Trained a regression model using scikit-learn
* Evaluated model performance using metrics like R² and MAE
* Improved the model by refining features and preprocessing steps

Outcome:

* Successfully transformed raw, messy data into a clean, structured dataset ready for machine learning
* Built and evaluated a predictive model with strong performance
* Gained practical understanding of the full pipeline from data cleaning to model evaluation

This work strengthened my ability to handle real datasets and apply machine learning effectively in a practical scenario.
